latestIgtvVideos.title: Puff using a crimp and tease technique
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Not everyone is blessed with  voluminous luxe hair 

Using a crimper instantly adds noticeable volume in the hair.

I am not a fan of textured hair so crimping near the roots lifts from underneath and leaves a natural voluminous look on the top

 The major advantage of this technique is the puff stays in place until you remove it

Pair it with a low bun hairstyle to achieve a classy look and I suggest this technique only for occasional use because heat on hair everyday  leaves damage

products used:
Ikonic mini crimper
tail comb 
bobby pins

earrings @anikalan_artjewellery

Okay, here goes my first makeup video.

Donut bun
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Things you will need: 
Medium size Donut bun
Hair pins
U pins
Few rubber bands/elastics

1.Teasing/ Back combing : I have backcombed to avoid my hair falling flat on the crown. This step can be completely skipped if u already have a fuller hair or if you are making a side partition in the front.

2. Donut bun : make sure you buy medium sized bun. If the bun is too big there won't be space for flowers. If the bun is too small it will lack volume.

3 U pins : only the U pins can firmly hold the donut bun in place. So a strict no no to normal hair pins

4. Rubber bands : If you are new to styling get help from someone to put the band around the bun to get a neater look

5. Do not hesitate to use a lot of pins to tuck all the extra hair and flowers. A secured hairstyle = a confident you🙂

Save this video for future reference and share it to the person who you think will help you create this look.
